article.description: Freddie Owens hit a last-second shot to catapult Wisconsin into the Sweet 16.
article.headline: Owens not only plays, but hits last-second winner
article.linkText: Badgers beat Tulsa in last second
article.story: TULSA, Okla. (AP) -- Jason Parker had 21 points and Jarius Glenn added 19 in Tulsa's 84-76 win over Athletes First in exhibition play Sunday. Parker had three rebounds, five assists and was 3-7 from the three point line. Glenn had five rebounds, seven assists and shot 56 percent from the field. John Wood scored 24 points for Athletes First. Wood had five rebounds and shot 6-10 from the three point line. Louis Truscott added 13 points for the Athletes. Truscott had five rebounds and one assist. Tulsa gave up 19 points off turnovers, but made up for it with 16 fast break points. Athletes gave up 15 points on turnovers and had no fast break points.
